description:
I was in my room trying to do my first product photo and the light was bad and I was desperate to have a beautiful result. I tried to create a lightbox without success. At one point, I just look around and focused on the Beauty that I saw and NOT on what I was missing… I saw this incredible chandelier with diamonds and I put the necklace on it! 
Jewels pictures are very difficult and I had to:
1. Change attitude and be positive and creative.
2. Realize that feeling is more important than thinking in photography.
3. Revise all basics of photography.
4. Know how to edit RAW files.
:)
